Analysis of the Target Image

• Block Count & Layers  
  – There are 6 total blocks.  
  – The lower (front) “layer” is made of 2 red arch‐shaped blocks side by side.  
  – Behind them (forming a second row) are 4 green upright rectangular blocks.  

• Spatial Arrangement  
  – The two red arches sit next to each other with the arch openings facing front.  
  – All four green blocks stand vertically in a row behind the red arches, forming a “backrest.”  

Selecting the Required Blocks

From the block dictionary:  
1. Red Arch Blocks  
   – Use index 1 for the left red arch (arch facing front as shown).  
   – Use index 2 for the right red arch (same shape/orientation but mirrored).  
2. Green Upright Blocks  
   – Use index 11 (the tall green block) for all four upright green pieces.  

Assembly Order

Below is one straightforward way to place them:

{
  Step1: Move block with index 1
  Step2: Move block with index 2
  Step3: Move block with index 11
  Step4: Move block with index 11
  Step5: Move block with index 11
  Step6: Move block with index 11
}
